x4freetext: 6-mil thick CsI(Tl) crystal cemented to
a Dumont 6291 photomultiplier tube.
The target gas was nitrogen, enriched to either 95%
or 98% in 15N.
The proton beam from an electrostatic
generator was collimated and allowed to enter the
target chamber through a nickel foil, 1000 A thick.
Scattered and reaction particles were detected by
CsI(Tl) crystal. Reaction gamma rays were detected
with a fixed, conventional NaI(Tl) crystal detector.
The yield of a particular process was obtained
by adding the number of counts under a peak. Since a
4.43-Mev gamma ray appears for every alpha1 particle,
the gamma-ray yield was a convenient monitor on the
incident proton energy.
